Let's take a look at the opening ceremony
that took place early this morning.

483
00:37:07,394 --> 00:37:12,691
Sochi has begun the first of its
17 day festivities under the spotlight.

484
00:37:13,984 --> 00:37:17,455
But we, here at YGN,
believe that our priority lies within

485
00:37:17,684 --> 00:37:21,233
bringing you the news
of the explosion

486
00:37:21,343 --> 00:37:24,363
at the waste factory that occurred
on the last 28th.

487
00:37:25,243 --> 00:37:27,543
We will reveal the identity of those
that are responsible

488
00:37:27,643 --> 00:37:30,009
who may otherwise have remained buried
under the glare of festivities.

489
00:37:30,149 --> 00:37:33,114
We believe that the core of the news

490
00:37:33,224 --> 00:37:36,114
is to convey the voices of
the victims' and their grieving families.

491
00:37:37,194 --> 00:37:41,554
The real cause of the fire and explosion
has finally been revealed.

492
00:37:41,994 --> 00:37:45,544
It was a gas explosion caused
by a leak from illegal chemical waste.

493
00:37:45,891 --> 00:37:48,604
Reporter Jang Hyun-gyu
brings you the exclusive.

494
00:37:48,695 --> 00:37:49,761
Cause of Factory Fire Revealed

495
00:37:49,852 --> 00:37:53,084
I'm on the scene of Hangang-gu factory
which claimed the lives of 40 people

496
00:37:53,184 --> 00:37:56,057
and injured many others
through a mysterious explosive fire.

497
00:37:56,444 --> 00:37:59,038
Even though it was speculated
that it was caused by gas vapors,

498
00:37:59,129 --> 00:38:03,849
an explosion was a piece of a mystery
that we initially couldn't solve.

499
00:38:04,328 --> 00:38:08,338
But after looking into the footage found
from a black box that YGN acquired,

500
00:38:08,438 --> 00:38:11,928
it was found that a fleet of trucks
containing illegal chemical waste

501
00:38:12,028 --> 00:38:14,718
were seen entering
the site of the factory property.

502
00:38:14,818 --> 00:38:18,728
Are you guys doing a good job
of investigating this case?

503
00:38:18,978 --> 00:38:22,368
YGN is going to continue covering
the case until the culprits are caught.

504
00:38:22,468 --> 00:38:25,738
-So stay sharp on the case.
-Yes, Sir!

505
00:38:26,208 --> 00:38:30,988
Officer Ahn, who was blamed for not
having thoroughly investigated the site

506
00:38:31,088 --> 00:38:33,798
has been cleared free of any blame
for the factory explosion.

507
00:38:34,448 --> 00:38:37,598
The true cause of the explosion
and the fire at the factory

508
00:38:37,698 --> 00:38:42,908
was due to the illegal chemical waste
brought to the factory two hours after.

509
00:38:42,999 --> 00:38:45,798
Illegal chemical waste that the factory
tried to get rid of secretly,

510
00:38:45,898 --> 00:38:49,075
was leaked and contaminated
all the nearby land and water.

511
00:38:49,208 --> 00:38:50,228
Water Control Team

512
00:38:50,338 --> 00:38:52,173
Go investigate the nearby sites.

513
00:38:52,264 --> 00:38:53,406
Han River Water Control Team

514
00:38:53,497 --> 00:38:55,388
With all the coverage
on the news station,

515
00:38:55,488 --> 00:38:58,228
we'll be in big trouble
if the inspectors decide to visit.

516
00:38:58,328 --> 00:39:01,698
After YGN's report, the prosecution
is now in full investigative mode.

517
00:39:01,918 --> 00:39:05,168
Prosecutors’ Office has summoned.

518
00:39:05,268 --> 00:39:08,238
Congressman Kim Kyung-woo
for questioning this afternoon.

519
00:39:08,938 --> 00:39:11,618
Prosecutors’ Office have confiscated
evidence from the residences

520
00:39:11,718 --> 00:39:14,198
of 10 individuals who were related
to the factory case

521
00:39:14,298 --> 00:39:16,450
and it supports the claim
of Congressman Kim accepting bribery

522
00:39:16,541 --> 00:39:18,191
as hush money
to dump illegal chemical waste.

523
00:39:18,939 --> 00:39:24,092
If it is ruled that Senator Kim Kyung-woo
is guilty of accepting these bribes,

524
00:39:24,183 --> 00:39:26,184
then Senator Kim will lose
his senate position.

525
00:39:30,039 --> 00:39:32,073
Reporter Ki Ha-myung reporting for YGN.

526
00:39:37,839 --> 00:39:39,969
Senator Kim Kyung-woo

527
00:39:43,863 --> 00:39:45,561
Yes, Sir.

528
00:39:47,199 --> 00:39:50,149
It's just an informal summon,
so don't worry about it so much.

529
00:39:52,224 --> 00:39:54,388
I did my best to stop this
from leaking out.

530
00:39:56,750 --> 00:39:59,829
Yes, I'll visit you soon.

531
00:40:02,434 --> 00:40:04,845
Why is YGN doing this?
Have they lost their minds?

532
00:40:04,936 --> 00:40:07,926
Why are they bothering me with this
instead of focusing on the Olympics?

533
00:40:08,017 --> 00:40:09,869
Did they totally ignore
their viewers’ ratings?

534
00:40:13,054 --> 00:40:14,279
They’re getting on my nerves.

535
00:40:16,736 --> 00:40:20,529
Those people have just cost me
one of my congressmen.

536
00:40:22,791 --> 00:40:24,952
We are now halfway through
the Olympics.

537
00:40:25,466 --> 00:40:29,009
The fervent cheers and glory of the event
reaches us through the news every day.

538
00:40:29,714 --> 00:40:34,428
But 17 deceased victims and their families

539
00:40:34,519 --> 00:40:37,149
cannot join in on this.

540
00:40:37,972 --> 00:40:40,909
There are those who are hoping
that the truth of the injustice done

541
00:40:40,999 --> 00:40:43,559
to these victims remains buried under
the fervor of this cheer.

542
00:40:44,004 --> 00:40:46,907
Those are none other than the culprits
that are responsible for this tragedy.

543
00:40:48,667 --> 00:40:53,889
Until their identities come to light
and are punished for it,

544
00:40:54,428 --> 00:40:58,419
we will continue to maintain our focus
and bring you all the updates on the case.

545
00:41:14,449 --> 00:41:17,041
I wish they would've done this
during dad's case, too.

546
00:41:22,579 --> 00:41:24,139
Right?

547
00:41:28,969 --> 00:41:30,389
Yes, you're right.

548
00:41:34,380 --> 00:41:36,212
I didn't like reporters.

549
00:41:37,543 --> 00:41:41,889
And I used to wish that all reporters
would just disappear from this earth.

550
00:41:45,535 --> 00:41:46,719
But now I'm glad.

551
00:41:47,239 --> 00:41:48,879
I'm glad that we became reporters.

552
00:41:51,529 --> 00:41:52,669
Yeah.

553
00:41:53,469 --> 00:41:56,579
Is it... all over now?

554
00:41:59,363 --> 00:42:01,509
No, this is only the beginning.

555
00:42:02,793 --> 00:42:05,979
Because I still have
too many questions to ask.

556
00:42:22,199 --> 00:42:24,619
The cheer for Athlete Lee Gyu-hyuk?

557
00:42:24,719 --> 00:42:27,919
Yes.
I understand.

558
00:42:34,924 --> 00:42:36,289
I can see you back there.

559
00:42:37,339 --> 00:42:38,239
Why are you hiding?

560
00:42:39,016 --> 00:42:40,644
Because I'm embarrassed.

561
00:42:42,919 --> 00:42:44,253
Embarrassed about what?

562
00:42:44,711 --> 00:42:47,249
You guys are continuing to report
real news updates on the case

563
00:42:47,604 --> 00:42:50,427
and we're just repeating
whatever we're told by the police.

564
00:42:51,269 --> 00:42:53,969
-Are you feeling sorry about it?
-Yeah.

565
00:42:54,109 --> 00:42:57,829
I feel sorry to Chan-soo, and
to the grieving families of the victims

566
00:42:57,929 --> 00:42:58,939
And...

567
00:43:00,447 --> 00:43:01,400
Leave me out of it.

568
00:43:02,208 --> 00:43:04,949
I really can't stand hearing you
telling me that you're sorry anymore.

569
00:43:16,111 --> 00:43:17,453
Ma'am, Sir?

570
00:43:17,544 --> 00:43:20,986
You have to give us the interview
right after the race is over, okay?

571
00:43:21,469 --> 00:43:23,009
Go for it, Lee Gyu-hyuk!

572
00:43:23,531 --> 00:43:27,399
Get on that interview with the family
as soon as he wins the gold medal.

573
00:43:28,367 --> 00:43:30,954
It's very likely that the mom will cry,
so make sure to catch that moment.

574
00:43:31,054 --> 00:43:33,594
-Okay.
-It's starting!

575
00:43:34,701 --> 00:43:38,234
I've been to the homes
of three separate gold medalists.

576
00:43:38,900 --> 00:43:40,174
It was all for nothing.

577
00:43:41,527 --> 00:43:42,894
I went to four.

578
00:43:43,649 --> 00:43:46,034
I even went to Itaewon yesterday
and asked a bunch of Russians

579
00:43:46,134 --> 00:43:48,524
'do you know kimchi?'
at least a hundred times.

580
00:43:54,892 --> 00:43:57,174
My dear reporters!
Good, you're all here.

581
00:43:57,274 --> 00:43:59,164
Thanks to all of you,
my name has been cleared!

582
00:44:00,154 --> 00:44:01,594
And I can sleep in peace again.

583
00:44:02,434 --> 00:44:05,124
Joon-hee, tell everyone
how thankful you are.

584
00:44:05,972 --> 00:44:07,617
Thank you.

585
00:44:08,402 --> 00:44:09,524
Yeah.

586
00:44:09,615 --> 00:44:12,900
Hey, MSC totally ditched your dad
to focus on the Olympics news.

587
00:44:13,242 --> 00:44:16,682
I think only we have earned the right
to accept those oranges.

588
00:44:19,162 --> 00:44:21,755
Knock it off.
We only do what our bosses tell us to do.

589
00:44:21,855 --> 00:44:24,642
We would have had to cover the Olympics
if we had worked for MSC.

590
00:44:24,742 --> 00:44:26,862
Are you taking In-ha's side right now?

591
00:44:27,562 --> 00:44:29,962
Your devotion to her is enough
to bring tears to my eyes

592
00:44:30,062 --> 00:44:31,838
and my self-pity
is bringing on even more tears!

593
00:44:36,852 --> 00:44:39,362
-What is wrong with her?
-I don't know.

594
00:44:39,462 --> 00:44:43,972
-She scares me once in a while.
-No, Yu-rae is right.

595
00:44:44,372 --> 00:44:46,452
I'm too ashamed to even face you,
Chan-soo.

596
00:44:46,562 --> 00:44:49,462
I can't believe MSC hasn't said
a single blip about the case.

597
00:44:49,572 --> 00:44:50,852
Does that make any sense?

598
00:44:50,952 --> 00:44:53,742
I know what you're feeling inside,
so don't blame yourself for it, my friend.

599
00:44:54,182 --> 00:44:57,845
And thanks to Mr Seo Bum-jo,
I'm no longer mad at MSC News.

600
00:44:59,352 --> 00:45:00,405
What do you mean by that?

601
00:45:01,651 --> 00:45:07,801
Mr Seo Bum-jo gave us a really big
envelope of cash for our son's party.

602
00:45:08,601 --> 00:45:10,241
Where is he?

603
00:45:14,981 --> 00:45:18,141
I noticed that there are many similarities
to the case from 13 years ago.

604
00:45:18,241 --> 00:45:21,351
Also that it was a waste factory
that exploded by illegal chemical waste.

605
00:45:21,451 --> 00:45:24,811
Looking at all these reports together,
they seem very awkwardly put together.

606
00:45:24,911 --> 00:45:27,681
As if the focus was purposely
driven onto your father.

607
00:45:27,781 --> 00:45:30,931
You said Ms Song Cha-ok left her phone
at your place 13 years ago, right?

608
00:45:31,041 --> 00:45:32,581
Do you remember the date
of that visit?

609
00:45:32,681 --> 00:45:34,771
October 23rd, 2000.

610
00:45:34,871 --> 00:45:37,731
My mother passed away
on October 22nd, 2000.

611
00:45:37,831 --> 00:45:40,551
If it is ruled
that Congressman Kim Kyung-woo

612
00:45:40,651 --> 00:45:43,441
is indeed guilty of
accepting those bribes...

613
00:45:54,861 --> 00:45:55,693
Son!

614
00:45:57,781 --> 00:45:59,542
What are you doing here?

615
00:46:01,771 --> 00:46:04,861
How silly of me to ask such a thing.
Of course my son should come home.

616
00:46:05,655 --> 00:46:07,927
What brings you by?
Do you need something?

617
00:46:08,091 --> 00:46:09,356
No, I don't need anything.

618
00:46:10,441 --> 00:46:11,665
I just had to ask you something.

619
00:46:12,111 --> 00:46:13,689
I wonder what it could be?

620
00:46:14,564 --> 00:46:17,341
You're scaring me with that serious look
on your face.

621
00:46:17,441 --> 00:46:18,841
Why would you be scared?

622
00:46:18,931 --> 00:46:21,442
Do you already have a hunch
about what I'm here to ask you?

623
00:46:23,711 --> 00:46:26,817
You had a meeting with Ms Song here
at the house 13 years ago.

624
00:46:27,621 --> 00:46:31,839
-Son, I've already told you...
-That wasn't the question.

625
00:46:32,473 --> 00:46:34,311
I'm just here to tell you the truth
which I've verified myself.

626
00:46:36,941 --> 00:46:38,781
The recent factory explosion case...

627
00:46:38,881 --> 00:46:41,667
It's extremely similar
to Ki Ho-sang's case from 13 years ago.

628
00:46:42,440 --> 00:46:44,981
An innocent bystander was framed
to be guilty for the accident...

629
00:46:45,121 --> 00:46:48,073
and when the clues were finally found,
other issues came up to bury it.

630
00:46:48,401 --> 00:46:52,001
Ms Song Cha-ok was the one
who directed the flow of the story then

631
00:46:52,101 --> 00:46:53,521
and the same has occurred again.

632
00:46:53,864 --> 00:46:57,698
And as the result, Ki Ho Sang's family
was completely ruined.

633
00:46:57,911 --> 00:47:01,290
And the very next day,
on October 23rd, 2000...

634
00:47:02,161 --> 00:47:04,164
you met with Ms Song Cha-ok.

635
00:47:04,841 --> 00:47:08,466
I have evidence that you met with Ms Song
again after the recent accident.

636
00:47:08,811 --> 00:47:10,821
What is it that you're trying to say?

637
00:47:12,481 --> 00:47:15,932
Turns out Congressman Kim Kyung-ho
was pulling the strings behind this case.

638
00:47:16,171 --> 00:47:19,149
I'm close enough to him
to address him as an uncle.

639
00:47:19,571 --> 00:47:22,210
And I know that he has
an even closer relationship with you.

640
00:47:22,687 --> 00:47:24,051
So?

641
00:47:24,341 --> 00:47:28,401
Are you saying that I'm somehow related
to those cases?

642
00:47:28,640 --> 00:47:29,741
Yes.

643
00:47:31,134 --> 00:47:33,464
Ms Song, Congressman Kim Kyung-ho...

644
00:47:34,497 --> 00:47:35,336
and you.

645
00:47:36,416 --> 00:47:40,551
I believe that the three of you
are related to those cases.

646
00:47:41,484 --> 00:47:44,091
-Am I wrong?
-Didn't I tell you?

647
00:47:44,871 --> 00:47:47,636
-That you can't treat me like a reporter.
-Mother!

648
00:47:48,550 --> 00:47:51,531
Come ask again after you quit
being a reporter, and I'll answer it then.

649
00:47:55,601 --> 00:47:59,979
Asking questions was all that we can do
with nothing but a suspicion.

650
00:48:03,958 --> 00:48:05,882
Even though those questions
may have seemed powerless...

651
00:48:08,791 --> 00:48:12,510
Yes, it's me. I think we need
to remain cautious for now.

652
00:48:13,141 --> 00:48:15,019
Senator Kim was taken in for questioning.

653
00:48:16,165 --> 00:48:19,511
And my son keeps asking me questions
about the case from 13 years ago.

654
00:48:19,611 --> 00:48:21,121
It's starting to get on my nerves.

655
00:48:21,261 --> 00:48:22,589
The more questions that were asked,

656
00:48:22,680 --> 00:48:24,269
the more they tried to hide their answers.

657
00:48:24,592 --> 00:48:27,792
Just in case, get rid of everything
that could incriminate us.

658
00:48:27,892 --> 00:48:29,674
And do not contact me for a while.

659
00:48:30,672 --> 00:48:31,939
Yes, Ma'am.

660
00:48:33,102 --> 00:48:35,912
And in the end, their secrets that
they tried so hard to keep hidden...

661
00:48:40,392 --> 00:48:42,652
would become the key
to unlocking those answers.

662
00:48:51,412 --> 00:48:52,682
It's about Ms Song.

663
00:48:52,782 --> 00:48:54,152
Did she lose something?

664
00:48:54,262 --> 00:48:56,882
-She keeps searching for something.
-I don't know.

665
00:48:57,022 --> 00:49:00,412
She told me that it was nothing,
but I guess it is something.

666
00:49:00,762 --> 00:49:02,482
Whatever it is,
she's still looking for it.

667
00:49:12,962 --> 00:49:14,257
I was pretty surprised.

668
00:49:14,712 --> 00:49:17,032
I didn't think you'd give up
your seat as a news anchor.

669
00:49:17,132 --> 00:49:18,932
No, can't be.

670
00:49:35,812 --> 00:49:38,492
This must be for the upcoming
Olympics news report?

671
00:49:38,602 --> 00:49:39,622
Yes.

672
00:49:39,722 --> 00:49:43,432
By any chance...
have you seen my old cellphone?

673
00:49:43,852 --> 00:49:45,122
Excuse me?

674
00:49:45,582 --> 00:49:49,532
I thought maybe you accidentally took it
when you helped me pick up my things.

675
00:49:53,270 --> 00:49:55,572
Yes, I guess I must've taken it.

676
00:49:59,438 --> 00:50:03,452
-Why would you have taken it?
-Because I was curious.

677
00:50:03,680 --> 00:50:05,501
I was curious to see what I sent
in those text messages.

678
00:50:06,142 --> 00:50:08,696
That's ridiculous.
When will you bring it back?

679
00:50:08,787 --> 00:50:09,917
I'll bring it to you tomorrow.

680
00:50:11,932 --> 00:50:14,275
There are many awkward phrasings
in here. Go through it again.

681
00:50:21,888 --> 00:50:23,650
-Choi In-ha.
-Yeah?

682
00:50:23,842 --> 00:50:26,256
I need you to give me that cellphone.

683
00:50:26,742 --> 00:50:27,874
Why?

684
00:50:28,627 --> 00:50:30,942
Don't ask, and just give it to me.
It was mine to begin with.

685
00:50:31,042 --> 00:50:32,322
What's wrong?

686
00:50:32,422 --> 00:50:35,502
Why are you and Ms Song both suddenly
so interested in that cellphone?

687
00:50:35,602 --> 00:50:37,092
You don't need to know why.

688
00:50:37,192 --> 00:50:38,729
Just hand it over.

689
00:50:40,742 --> 00:50:42,294
Tell me the reason,
and I'll give it to you.

690
00:50:45,339 --> 00:50:48,189
You know there are manipulation
of the public attention,

691
00:50:48,289 --> 00:50:50,103
in this case and the case
from 13 years ago, right?

692
00:50:51,167 --> 00:50:52,597
Yeah.

693
00:50:53,523 --> 00:50:59,593
I believe that Ms Song and my mother
are related to both those cases.

694
00:51:01,493 --> 00:51:04,843
-Yeah, me too.
-And that evidence...

695
00:51:05,273 --> 00:51:09,412
might be on that cellphone.

696
00:51:10,546 --> 00:51:12,403
On the cellphone?
Why do you think that?

697
00:51:17,073 --> 00:51:18,133
When I thought about it,

698
00:51:18,233 --> 00:51:21,221
I thought it weird that only the texts
you sent were on that phone.

699
00:51:21,897 --> 00:51:24,746
Why aren't there any other messages
or call logs other than yours?

700
00:51:25,973 --> 00:51:28,923
I'm sure that Ms Song
had that cellphone even before then.

701
00:51:33,393 --> 00:51:35,942
Then are you saying that she
purposely deleted all the other messages?

702
00:51:37,843 --> 00:51:39,463
Maybe.

703
00:52:04,023 --> 00:52:06,133
No more messages

704
00:52:24,280 --> 00:52:25,489
Data Return

705
00:52:37,063 --> 00:52:40,635
Would it be possible to retrieve
all the deleted texts and call logs?

706
00:52:41,564 --> 00:52:43,171
This model is from 1999.

707
00:52:43,403 --> 00:52:44,903
It’s like a piece of cake.

708
00:52:45,003 --> 00:52:47,873
Address book, SNS, MMS messaging,
and all the call logs...

709
00:52:47,973 --> 00:52:49,098
All those can be retrieved.

710
00:52:49,313 --> 00:52:51,183
How long will that take?

711
00:52:51,513 --> 00:52:54,033
I'm not sure.
I won't know until I start the process.

712
00:52:54,133 --> 00:52:57,843
It may take anywhere from a few hours
to a couple of days, at most.

713
00:52:58,353 --> 00:53:00,553
If you're in a rush for it,
then I can email you the results.

714
00:53:01,013 --> 00:53:03,015
Then can you please email it to me?

715
00:53:05,303 --> 00:53:07,283
I just need you to fill out this form.

716
00:53:07,923 --> 00:53:11,783
But you do realize that your name
must match the phone account holder?

717
00:53:11,883 --> 00:53:13,232
If it doesn't, then I can't recover it.

718
00:53:13,603 --> 00:53:14,813
Excuse me?

719
00:53:14,923 --> 00:53:16,343
The account holder?

720
00:53:30,043 --> 00:53:33,353
I guess you need to be here for us
to retrieve the contents of this phone.

721
00:53:33,453 --> 00:53:35,053
What did you try to do?

722
00:53:35,343 --> 00:53:37,563
You were trying to retrieve the texts
without me knowing about it?

723
00:53:38,493 --> 00:53:40,263
That's...

724
00:53:41,353 --> 00:53:42,713
If what you're saying is true,

725
00:53:42,813 --> 00:53:44,859
it'll hurt you more than
it will hurt me.

726
00:53:45,828 --> 00:53:49,479
So I thought it would be better
if only I would get hurt from it.

727
00:53:50,943 --> 00:53:54,613
Thanks for worrying about me,
but I'm not that weak of a person.

728
00:53:58,063 --> 00:53:59,514
What forms do I need to fill out?

729
00:54:03,312 --> 00:54:05,763
There's a fellow reporter
whose name is Cha Woo-chul.

730
00:54:05,863 --> 00:54:09,233
He did a report on the contamination,
and I looked into...

731
00:54:10,863 --> 00:54:12,389
You can stop with your explanations.

732
00:54:12,623 --> 00:54:13,983
I can watch the news from in here.

733
00:54:15,203 --> 00:54:17,653
-I saw it all.
-Really?

734
00:54:17,793 --> 00:54:20,987
-You saw me reporting live?
-Yeah.

735
00:54:21,773 --> 00:54:24,433
But you looked a little too stiff.

736
00:54:24,533 --> 00:54:26,543
-I could tell that you were a rookie.
-Jae-myung!

737
00:54:29,029 --> 00:54:30,601
I'm really glad that you're a reporter.

738
00:54:32,213 --> 00:54:34,323
What's this?
You're trying to sweeten your blow?

739
00:54:34,413 --> 00:54:38,873
At the very least, I know that I can
trust the news that you report.

740
00:54:45,193 --> 00:54:46,973
Because it burns hot in there...

741
00:54:48,633 --> 00:54:50,289
while it remains cold up there.

742
00:54:52,813 --> 00:54:54,286
The opposite of someone else I know.

743
00:54:55,913 --> 00:54:57,413
Who?

744
00:54:57,503 --> 00:55:00,803
-Ms Song?
-Yeah.

745
00:55:15,543 --> 00:55:17,953
Hello? Have you recovered the phone?

746
00:55:18,053 --> 00:55:21,193
Yes, I just emailed it to the address
that you left with me.

747
00:55:21,303 --> 00:55:23,993
-You can check it now.
-Thank you.

748
00:55:30,923 --> 00:55:33,613
-Did you get the phone call, too?
-Yeah.

749
00:55:38,133 --> 00:55:40,653
Are there that many messages
deleted from the phone?

750
00:55:41,713 --> 00:55:43,023
Yeah.

751
00:55:45,623 --> 00:55:47,433
Who is 'The Chairwoman'?

752
00:55:50,923 --> 00:55:52,693
It's my mother.

753
00:55:57,343 --> 00:55:58,593
Are you sure?

754
00:55:59,973 --> 00:56:01,193
Yeah.

755
00:56:02,393 --> 00:56:04,693
This is my mother's old phone number.

756
00:56:05,203 --> 00:56:07,263
The last four digits are still the same.

757
00:56:14,014 --> 00:56:16,413
Open up the messages and let's see.

758
00:56:27,353 --> 00:56:30,310
We need to divert the attention.

759
00:56:31,200 --> 00:56:35,313
Turn the focus on Ki Ho-sang
and turn him into the bad guy.

760
00:56:35,513 --> 00:56:38,913
Why do you think he ordered such a thing?
Did he have his sights set on a promotion?

761
00:56:39,013 --> 00:56:41,383
-He isn't that type of a man!
-Use his family if needed.

762
00:56:41,513 --> 00:56:43,363
Are you saying that your father
isn't at fault?

763
00:56:43,473 --> 00:56:46,322
How fortunate that
we have found a Pinocchio witness!

764
00:56:47,159 --> 00:56:50,133
-Use that unique characteristic...
-The witness said that he saw your father.

765
00:56:50,233 --> 00:56:52,563
The witness is a Pinocchio,
so it couldn't have been a lie.

766
00:56:52,663 --> 00:56:56,983
I'm positive that it was him.
I'm a Pinocchio, so I can't lie.

767
00:56:57,083 --> 00:57:01,563
Do what you can to fan the rage of
the nationwide public as much as possible.

768
00:57:01,663 --> 00:57:03,493
You must be happy your father's alive.

769
00:57:03,583 --> 00:57:10,113
But the crowd believes that it's too light
of a sentence for the deaths

770
00:57:10,223 --> 00:57:13,136
of the nine firemen
and are enraged for justice.

771
00:57:43,033 --> 00:57:45,383
Can you call yourself a reporter?

772
00:57:45,483 --> 00:57:47,813
Aside from you, who else knows about this?

773
00:57:48,263 --> 00:57:51,463
-Captain, as of today...
-Are you saying that you'll betray us?

774
00:57:51,563 --> 00:57:53,723
I'll reveal all the connections
between the parties.

775
00:57:53,823 --> 00:57:56,373
-As a mother.
-Who reported this information?

776
00:57:56,473 --> 00:57:59,163
-Miss Choi In-ha!
-Director Yeon has just told it.

777
00:57:59,263 --> 00:58:02,353
Tell me that I did okay.
Tell me I did the right thing, Dad!

778
00:58:02,453 --> 00:58:04,953
Yes, you did the right thing.
My daughter did the right thing!
